Atkins Rod-Doc
May 16 at 2:45 PM ·

The World has lost an Angel on Earth; a Community and School has lost one of its Champions. The Voyageur-Consortium Family appreciates one of our GREATEST Parent Advocates, Supporters, and Friends. The campus flags will fly half mast to honor and celebrate the life of Jamie Rutledge: Wife, Mother, Sister, Aunt, Relative, Friend, and All-around Wonderful Lady. post_text: The entire Voyageur School District from Kindergarten to 12th grade is simply amazing!!
shared_text:
Atkins Rod-Doc
April 24 at 1:05 PM ·

Voyageur Stakeholders Congratulations (families, staff, Board of Directors, The Romine Group, Authorizer (FSU) and most of all STUDENTS from 1999 to 2020 this is for and because of YOU!) U.S. News and World Report released its annual rankings of the Best High Schools in America, and not surprisingly, the top nine open-enrollment high schools in Detroit are all charter schools. Considered the gold standards of high school rankings, U.S. News and World Report uses a metric that looks at six factors: college readiness; reading and math proficiency; reading and math performance; underserved student performance; college curriculum breadth; and graduation rates. College readiness measures participation and performance on AP and IB exams.

post_text:
Voyageur Academy is here for you and we will continue to support one another. Our social workers, Mrs. Matthews and Ms White, are sharing weekly wellness resources as a part of our commitment to support our Voyageur families during this challenging time.

Please give us a call at our hotline (313) 748-4000 or message us here with any questions or concerns.

If you are in need of immediate support:

City of Detroit
Covid-19 Hotline
(313) 876-4000

The Michigan Department of Health and Human Services is operating a Warmline.
The warmline will operate seven days a week from 10 a.m. to 2 a.m. at 888-PEER-753 (888-733-7753). It is intended to serve individuals living with persistent mental health challenges including anxiety, depression and trauma.

Individuals in crisis, including those considering suicide, are urged to contact the Disaster Distress Helpline 24/7 at 800-985-5990 or the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 24/7 at 800-273-8255.

post_text: What a treat for Voyageur students to move from the music excellence of Mr. V and the art excellence of Ms. Barber. They can continue their creativity in the Performing & Visual Arts Department of the high school.
shared_text:
Atkins Rod-Doc is with Lisa McCall and 2 others.
March 12 at 10:44 PM ·

I know we brag a lot about Voyageur's Performing & Visual Arts Department...well here is one more reason why; the self portrait art project was a huge success as usual. It is so easy to identify each student. Mrs. Halpin is one of the best teachers on the planet, maybe the universe.🤔 This creative team of elective teachers are the best ever assembled at Voyageur and probably of any school in Michigan . Choir, dance, art, music, and drama bring out the highest level of creativity possible and connects the students' spirits with the soul of Voyageur!

February 22 at 12:46 AM ·

News Alert...Fathers missing in Detroit...Not! just all at the Voyageur2020 Daddy Daughter Dance. 250+ daddies and daughters in the house. The dads' looked amazing, and their little princesses were stunning. Nothing like the paternal love of a father for his daughter. My favorite part was when they pronounced their love to one another ..and then danced to Luther Vandross' "Dance with my Father" ...Voyageur Dads in the house!! Great job V-Team and committee for putting together such a wonderful program!

Explore the world
Be yourself

We need to PRAY TOGETHER
We need to LOVE EACH OTHER
We need to BE LIONS

post_text: Pee Wee Hoops Season is at it again! Great job Coach Townsend and AD Gonzalez!
shared_text:
Atkins Rod-Doc
February 9 at 11:07 PM ·

Pee Wee Hoops in the Voyageur School District. We do start them young. (We are thinking about a mini-pee wee league that starts them at the age of 1)😉. Coach Townsend and high school athletes managed the leagues which runs for six weeks. What better way to prepare for the future than start in kindergarten. Coach Townsend said, "Today was great! There was so much energy in the room. The high school students were beyond helpful and excited to teach the K-4 scholars. Great turnout with the parents. The scholars were so excited. I was pleased with the parents bringing the scholars to learn and be a part of something great! This is only the beginning!

Atkins Rod-Doc
February 1 at 10:09 PM ·

#DadGirl at its best is coming to the Voyageur School District for Kindergarten to 8th grades as we celebrate that special relationship between Fathers and Daughters. Kisses and hugs from a daughter are more valuable than silver and gold. Nothing on the planet melts men's hearts more that the precious and innocent love from daddy's little girl! A gift from God it is...daughters, make your fathers' day and give him a hug and kiss like you did as a child..it will make his day like nothing else! I know from experience!
